# React Component Structure

This rule ensures consistent structure for React components.

## Valid Example

```typescript
import { type FC } from 'react';

interface ProductTableProps {
  products: Product[];
  onRefresh: () => void;
}

export const ProductTable: FC<ProductTableProps> = ({ products, onRefresh }) => {
  // Component logic here
  return (
    <div>
      {/* Component JSX */}
    </div>
  );
};
```

## Invalid Example

```typescript
// Missing type annotations and inconsistent structure
export default function ProductTable(props) {
  return (
    <div>
      {props.products.map(p => (
        <div key={p.id}>{p.name}</div>
      ))}
    </div>
  );
}
```

## Guidelines

1. Use named exports with explicit FC type
2. Define Props interface
3. Use TypeScript type annotations
4. Destructure props in component parameters
5. Place component logic before return statement
6. Use semantic HTML elements
7. Include proper accessibility attributes 